2026-04-16 12:11:16 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Power supply module cable pair between power module and control module'] hypothesis_explanation='The red LED in the control module is designed to turn on only when the 12 V and 0 V lines from the power supply are reversed at the control module input. Currently, the power‐supply green LED is off (no proper supply across its internal indicator), while the red LED on the control module is on. This combination strongly indicates that the two output leads from the power module have been cross‑connected to the input leads of the control module (polarity reversal between the modules). With this mis‑wiring, the control-module ‘inverted cables indicator’ LED sees a forward bias and lights, but the correct polarity is not present downstream, so the diode ahead of the load blocks current and the main lamp stays off.\n\nThe fault is therefore a configuration error on the cable pair between the power supply module and the control module: the two conductors are swapped. Reconnecting this pair with the correct polarity should restore normal operation (green LED on at the supply, red LED off at the control, and lamp on when the switch is closed).'
